Class AltWeakReference<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.ref.Reference<T>
      • java.lang.ref.WeakReference<T>
        • com.futurice.cascade.util.AltWeakReference<T>

  • public class AltWeakReference<T>
extends java.lang.ref.WeakReference<T>
    A WeakReference which also returns true as normal, and also if equality tests positive for two AltWeakReference objects pointed to. just as if it were the object to which it points

    Created by Paul Houghton on 23-03-2015.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object other)
        Test equality. The definition of equality is different from WeakReference. Two items are also equal if the items referenced are equal or if one of them is the item referenced. This helps to simplify some logic associated with WeakReference

        public int hashCode()
        Description copied from class: java.lang.Object
        Returns an integer hash code for this object. By contract, any two objects for which Object.equals(java.lang.Object) returns true must return the same hash code value. This means that subclasses of Object usually override both methods or neither method.

        Note that hash values must not change over time unless information used in equals comparisons also changes.

        See Writing a correct hashCode method if you intend implementing your own hashCode method.
